# PolarCoordinate -- geometry

The _PolarCoordinate_ type represents a pair of numbers designating a location in Polar coordinate space.

The usual mathematical notation is (r, theta), where r is the radius and theta the angle.

The ISO standardised notation is (rho, phi).

